First Lady Jill Biden addressed the National PTA Convention, expressing gratitude for their work in advocating for students. She emphasized the importance of unity between parents and educators and praised their collaboration during the challenges of virtual learning. Biden acknowledged the ongoing struggles faced by students due to the pandemic and highlighted the need for mental health and academic support. She also spoke about the issue of school safety and urged Congress to pass gun safety reform. Biden concluded by urging parents and educators to continue fighting for the well-being of children and thanked the PTA for their partnership.